<ol>
  <li>
    <p>calculate object_id from memory address
object_id returns half the objectâ€™s memory address, so you need to multiply by 2 to get the actual address. (Vice versa, divide memory address by 2 to get object_id)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>get reference of object by object_id
<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">obj = ObjectSpace._id2ref(object_id)</code></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>inspect referenced object
<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">obj.inspect</code></p>
  </li>
</ol>

